<subSubSection id="C31E654AFFB4FFE2FF7FE251FB03D2C1" pageId="6" pageNumber="45" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BBB36C1FFB4FFE2FF7FE251FB03D2C1" blockId="6.[151,1437,1295,2004]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis id="B970EAD3FFB4FFE2FF7FE251FEF9D27D" bold="true" box="[151,273,1295,1320]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Males of 
<taxonomicName id="4C044D42FFB4FFE2FE6EE24FFDEBD27D" box="[390,515,1297,1320]" class="Arachnida" family="Araneidae" genus="Micrathena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gaujoni">
<emphasis id="B970EAD3FFB4FFE2FE6EE24FFDEBD27D" box="[390,515,1297,1320]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">M. gaujoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differ from all other 
<taxonomicName id="4C044D42FFB4FFE2FD1EE24EFC91D27D" box="[758,889,1296,1320]" class="Arachnida" family="Araneidae" genus="Micrathena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B970EAD3FFB4FFE2FD1EE24EFC91D27D" box="[758,889,1296,1320]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">Micrathena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with a coxal hook by having an extremely long embolus projecting above the terminal apophysis and lying in a very large conductor, which occupies most of the tegulum in mesal view (
<figureCitation id="133F2A44FFB4FFE2FE4CE209FE1FD23A" box="[420,503,1367,1391]" captionStart="FIGURES 14 – 16" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1522,1545]" captionTargetBox="[178,1399,457,1491]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[165,1422,439,1498]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 14 – 16. Micrathena gaujoni Simon, 1897, male (UFMG 3355). 14 – 15, habitus: 14, lateral view; 15, dorsal view. 16, left palp, mesal view. Abbreviations: BH = basal hematodocha, BP = basal projection of the median apophysis, C = conductor, Cy = cymbium, E = embolus, M = median apophysis, PM = paramedian apophysis, R = radix, TA = terminal apophysis, TP = terminal apophysis projection. Scale bars: 14 – 15, 1 mm; 16, 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/205447/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">
Fig. 
<number id="3DCC24E6FFB4FFE2FE30E209FE1FD23A" box="[472,503,1367,1391]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45" value="16.0">16</number>
</figureCitation>
). This species is most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C044D42FFB4FFE2FC8CE207FB71D23A" authority="Levi" authorityName="Levi" authorityYear="1985" box="[868,1177,1367,1392]" class="Arachnida" family="Araneidae" genus="Micrathena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pilaton">
<emphasis id="B970EAD3FFB4FFE2FC8CE207FC30D225" box="[868,984,1368,1392]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">M. pilaton</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF954B30FFB4FFE2FC37E209FB71D23A" author="Levi" box="[991,1177,1367,1391]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45" refString="Levi, H. W. (1985) The spiny orb-weaver genera Micrathena and Chaetacis (Araneae: Araneidae). Bulletin of the Museum of Comparative Zoology, Harvard University 150, 429 - 618." type="journal article" year="1985">
Levi (
<bibRefCitation id="EF954B30FFB4FFE2FBC9E209FB71D23A" author="Levi" box="[1057,1177,1367,1391]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45" refString="Levi, H. W. (1985) The spiny orb-weaver genera Micrathena and Chaetacis (Araneae: Araneidae). Bulletin of the Museum of Comparative Zoology, Harvard University 150, 429 - 618." type="journal article" year="1985">
Levi 
<number id="3DCC24E6FFB4FFE2FBB5E209FB71D23A" box="[1117,1177,1367,1391]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45" value="1985.0">1985</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
: fig. 
<number id="3DCC24E6FFB4FFE2FB39E209FB18D23A" box="[1233,1264,1367,1391]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45" value="24.0">24</number>
), from which it differs by having a much larger terminal apophysis. For the female diagnosis see 
<bibRefCitation id="EF954B30FFB4FFE2FBCEE222FB0FD2C1" author="Levi" box="[1062,1255,1404,1428]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45" refString="Levi, H. W. (1985) The spiny orb-weaver genera Micrathena and Chaetacis (Araneae: Araneidae). Bulletin of the Museum of Comparative Zoology, Harvard University 150, 429 - 618." type="journal article" year="1985">
Levi (
<number id="3DCC24E6FFB4FFE2FB81E222FB4ED2C1" box="[1129,1190,1404,1428]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45" value="1985.0">1985</number>
: 
<number id="3DCC24E6FFB4FFE2FB58E222FB37D2C1" box="[1200,1247,1404,1428]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45" value="478.0">478</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C31E654AFFB4FFE3FF2FE2C1FBA4D649" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="46" pageId="6" pageNumber="45" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BBB36C1FFB4FFE2FF2FE2C1FCEED0E5" blockId="6.[151,1437,1295,2004]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis id="B970EAD3FFB4FFE2FF2FE2C1FEB1D2ED" bold="true" box="[199,345,1439,1464]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">Description.</emphasis>
Male from Estación Biológica Yanayacu, 
<collectingCountry id="F3137651FFB4FFE2FCD1E2C1FC71D2E2" box="[825,921,1439,1463]" name="Ecuador" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
, (
<collectionCode id="ED15AE04FFB4FFE2FC44E2C1FC17D2E2" box="[940,1023,1439,1463]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/z0ie-wfm6" name="Universidade Federal de Minas Gerais" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">UFMG</collectionCode>
<number id="3DCC24E6FFB4FFE2FBEEE2C1FBABD2E2" box="[1030,1091,1439,1463]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45" value="3355.0">3355</number>
). Carapace light brown, with a dark brown band on each side (
<figureCitation id="133F2A44FFB4FFE2FE13E29AFDA7D289" box="[507,591,1476,1500]" captionStart="FIGURES 14 – 16" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1522,1545]" captionTargetBox="[178,1399,457,1491]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[165,1422,439,1498]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 14 – 16. Micrathena gaujoni Simon, 1897, male (UFMG 3355). 14 – 15, habitus: 14, lateral view; 15, dorsal view. 16, left palp, mesal view. Abbreviations: BH = basal hematodocha, BP = basal projection of the median apophysis, C = conductor, Cy = cymbium, E = embolus, M = median apophysis, PM = paramedian apophysis, R = radix, TA = terminal apophysis, TP = terminal apophysis projection. Scale bars: 14 – 15, 1 mm; 16, 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/205447/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">
Fig. 
<number id="3DCC24E6FFB4FFE2FDD8E29AFDA7D289" box="[560,591,1476,1500]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45" value="14.0">14</number>
</figureCitation>
). Chelicerae, endites, labium and sternum brown. Legs yellow proximally, brown distally. Dorsum of abdomen white with a median pattern of dark brown markings (
<figureCitation id="133F2A44FFB4FFE2FB46E2B9FAECD2AA" box="[1198,1284,1511,1535]" captionStart="FIGURES 14 – 16" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1522,1545]" captionTargetBox="[178,1399,457,1491]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[165,1422,439,1498]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 14 – 16. Micrathena gaujoni Simon, 1897, male (UFMG 3355). 14 – 15, habitus: 14, lateral view; 15, dorsal view. 16, left palp, mesal view. Abbreviations: BH = basal hematodocha, BP = basal projection of the median apophysis, C = conductor, Cy = cymbium, E = embolus, M = median apophysis, PM = paramedian apophysis, R = radix, TA = terminal apophysis, TP = terminal apophysis projection. Scale bars: 14 – 15, 1 mm; 16, 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/205447/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">
Fig. 
<number id="3DCC24E6FFB4FFE2FB0DE2B9FAECD2AA" box="[1253,1284,1511,1535]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45" value="14.0">14</number>
</figureCitation>
); venter dark brown. Carapace with oval thoracic region, narrowest behind, a circular fovea and no dimples (
<figureCitation id="133F2A44FFB4FFE2FB2CE152FAF0D171" box="[1220,1304,1548,1572]" captionStart="FIGURES 14 – 16" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1522,1545]" captionTargetBox="[178,1399,457,1491]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[165,1422,439,1498]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 14 – 16. Micrathena gaujoni Simon, 1897, male (UFMG 3355). 14 – 15, habitus: 14, lateral view; 15, dorsal view. 16, left palp, mesal view. Abbreviations: BH = basal hematodocha, BP = basal projection of the median apophysis, C = conductor, Cy = cymbium, E = embolus, M = median apophysis, PM = paramedian apophysis, R = radix, TA = terminal apophysis, TP = terminal apophysis projection. Scale bars: 14 – 15, 1 mm; 16, 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/205447/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">
Fig. 
<number id="3DCC24E6FFB4FFE2FB11E152FAF0D171" box="[1273,1304,1548,1572]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45" value="14.0">14</number>
</figureCitation>
). First coxa with hook and second femur with corresponding prolateral groove. Tibiae and femora I and II markedly ornamented with macrosetae on the dorsal surface; tibia II with two ventral rows of robust macrosetae, femur II with a single, median, ventral row of macrosetae (
<figureCitation id="133F2A44FFB4FFE2FDB6E129FD5AD1DA" box="[606,690,1655,1679]" captionStart="FIGURES 14 – 16" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1522,1545]" captionTargetBox="[178,1399,457,1491]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[165,1422,439,1498]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 14 – 16. Micrathena gaujoni Simon, 1897, male (UFMG 3355). 14 – 15, habitus: 14, lateral view; 15, dorsal view. 16, left palp, mesal view. Abbreviations: BH = basal hematodocha, BP = basal projection of the median apophysis, C = conductor, Cy = cymbium, E = embolus, M = median apophysis, PM = paramedian apophysis, R = radix, TA = terminal apophysis, TP = terminal apophysis projection. Scale bars: 14 – 15, 1 mm; 16, 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/205447/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">
Fig. 
